President Muhammadu Buhari has signed a bill nullifying May 29 previously marked as a public holiday and recognizing June 12 as the official day for the celebration of democracy in the country.
With the bill now signed into law, June 12 has been officially declared as holiday.
Senior Special Assistant on National Assembly Matters (Senate), Senator Ita Enang, who disclosed this while briefing State House correspondents at the presidential villa, Abuja, said President Buhari assented to the law tagged Public Holiday Amendment bill.
He explained that the new law now allows a public holiday to be declared on June 12 every year, while May 29th will no longer be public holiday.
“May 29th will only be handing over date and working day. By the act amended and signed by Mr. President, May 29 is no more a public holiday. June 12 is now a public holiday and the country’s Democracy Day,” he said.
Tomorrow, 12th of June 2019 will be the first time the change of democracy day will be observed in the country.
Since return of democracy in 1999, May 29 had been observed as democracy day.